 F(a) = \int_0^u \sqrt{x^2+a^2}\;dx 
 \frac{d}{dx} \;\sqrt{a^2+x^2} = \frac{a}{\sqrt{x^2+a^2}} 
 F'(a) = \int_0^u \frac{a}{\sqrt{x^2+a^2}}\;dx =  -a\log a +a u\log\left(a + \sqrt{a^2+u^2}\right) 
 F(a) = \frac{-\log  \left( a \right) {a}^{2}+\log  \left( u+\sqrt {{a}^{2}+{u}^{2}}  \right) {a}^{2}+\sqrt {{a}^{2}+{u}^{2}}u}{2} 
